      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "SET ME FREE (6) ran a good race on debut at Geelong, bumping into a smart winner but doing well to hold second over the 1435m. She's bred to run a bit of a trip so getting to 1600m now suits nicely and with natural improvement she can go one better. TEMU TILLY (7) has been solid in three runs to date, sticking on well enough for second at Yarra Valley last time out. She'll roll forward and take some catching. CHARLECOTE MILL (3) put in a good effort when last seen at Kilmore over this trip, finding the line strongly. She'll be finishing quickly if the favoured ones go at each other in front. DUNDIVA (4) and KISSATTACK (5) are both on debut. Neither have trialled the house down but kick off over suitable trips, watch the market.",
